10 Sec. 4. The Director of Administrative Services is hereby
11 authorized and directed to draw his or her warrants upon the funds in the
12 state treasury enumerated in this act, in favor of the several
13 beneficiaries named in this act for the amount set opposite their
14 respective names, upon the presentation of proper vouchers therefor. The
15 several amounts appropriated in this act shall be in full payment of any
16 and all claims, rights, causes of action, damages, and demands of every
17 character and kind owing by or against the State of Nebraska, its
18 officers, agents, and employees, and their successors and assigns with
19 respect to each of the beneficiaries respectively in whose favor the
20 appropriations are made. The director shall not deliver any warrant for
21 any items appropriated in this act until a receipt and release in full,
22 releasing the State of Nebraska, its officers, employees, and agents, and
23 their successors and assigns, has been filed by each of the beneficiaries
24 respectively. Upon presentation of the warrants, the State Treasurer is
25 hereby directed to pay the same out of money in the General Fund or out
26 of money in other funds indicated in this act not otherwise appropriated.
27 Sec. 5. The following requests were filed by state agencies seeking
28 permission to write off certain accounts. The State Claims Board reviewed
29 and approved the following requests:
30 $856.00 for Request Number 2026-01512, made by the State Fire
31 Marshal.
